            "title": "A forma\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e9tica do psic\u00f3logo : ambiente acad\u00eamico e compet\u00eancia moral",
            "abstract": [
                "Esta obra aborda a problem\u00e1tica da forma\u00e7\u00e3o em Psicologia, especialmente quanto \u00e0 forma\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e9tica e moral para o exerc\u00edcio da profiss\u00e3o. Apresenta os conceitos, as diretrizes curriculares, a interdisciplinaridade, as metodologias ativas e o papel do professor; colaborando com a reflex\u00e3o de estudantes de Gradua\u00e7\u00e3o em Psicologia e em Educa\u00e7\u00e3o, de docentes, de institui\u00e7\u00f5es educacionais e de conselhos de classe preocupados com a forma\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e9tica da Psicologia no Brasil.  Ao abordar a forma\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e9tica do psic\u00f3logo, temos a vis\u00e3o das dimens\u00f5es assumidas por esse saber cient\u00edfico, quer no relacionamento consigo mesmo, quer nas rela\u00e7\u00f5es interpessoais, quer no posicionamento pol\u00edtico com a sociedade ou, ainda, na possibilidade da constru\u00e7\u00e3o de uma concep\u00e7\u00e3o cr\u00edtica do entorno. No processo ensino-aprendizagem, os est\u00e1gios supervisionados em Psicologia possibilitam a forma\u00e7\u00e3o de profissionais com maior capacidade de integra\u00e7\u00e3o entre teoria, t\u00e9cnica e pr\u00e1tica. Integra\u00e7\u00e3o essa que contribui para maior sensibilidade dos profissionais \u00e0s demandas, \u00e0 integralidade do outro e a seu papel social e \u00e9tico",
                "This work addresses the problem of training in Psychology, especially regarding ethical and moral training for the exercise of the profession. It presents concepts, curricular guidelines, interdisciplinarity, active methodologies and the role of the teacher; collaborating with the reflection of undergraduate students in Psychology and Education, teachers, educational institutions and class councils concerned with the ethical formation of Psychology in Brazil.  When approaching the ethical training of psychologists, we have a view of the dimensions assumed by this scientific knowledge, whether in the relationship with oneself, whether in interpersonal relationships, whether in the political position with society or, even, in the possibility of building a critical conception of the environment. In the teaching-learning process, supervised internships in Psychology enable the formation of professionals with greater capacity for integration between theory, technique and practice. This integration contributes to greater sensitivity of professionals to the demands, to the integrality of the other and to their social and ethical role"
            ],
